University highlights

 Ranked 7th in Top Universities Abroad


Oxford is consistently ranked one of the world’s top five universities
Oxford graduates include: More than 30 international leaders, 27 Nobel Prize winners, 26 British Prime Ministers
94% of Oxford leavers are employed, in further study, or both within six months after graduating
Almost 40% of total student body - over 8,400 students - are citizens of foreign countries, including 17% of undergraduates and 61% of graduate students
Students come from the USA (1,516), China (865), Germany (806), Canada (401), India (336), Australia (312), Italy (264), Ireland (232), Singapore (229) and France (219)
